…As Afe Babalola Donates N100m To Response Fund The second Coronavirus patient in Ekiti State has tested negative consecutively and has been discharged from isolation centre. This came as the founder of Afe Babalola University, Ado Ekiti (ABUAD) made a donation N100 million and 800 bags of rice to the state Covid-19 Response Resource Mobilization Committee. Governor Kayode Fayemi had last week appointed Chief Babalola, former Governors Segun Oni and Ayodele Fayose and 44 others as members of the committee set up to help mobilize resources to combat Covid-19 in the state. The Nigeria Center for Disease Control, (NCDC) had last week announced the new case of a 42 year-old male, Ekiti indigene, and was subsequently confirmed by state government. The discharged patient, who has been in isolation center was said to be travelling often by the nature of his job and have been to the airport in Lagos which could account for his infection. Fayemi who confirmed this on his Twitter handle, revealed that the second test performed on the patient was negative and the patient has subsequently been discharged. Fayemi tweeted: “Our second COVID-19 patient tested negative the second time and was discharged from our Infectious Disease Hospital today. “While thanking our team for a job well done, the job is not finished. Stay home, save lives.”, he advised. Fayemi tweeted further that the Ekiti CoviD 19 Response Committee held its inaugural meeting yesterday and made several concrete steps. “Our father, the Grand Patron,  Chief Afe Babalola (SAN) set the ball rolling with N100m donation and 800 bags of rice to the Food Bank. We are grateful”. 